node.text: Switch off, settle in… and relax! 🙏 From @southaustralia’s surreal salt lakes to the inviting shores of @queensland’s @visitfraserisland, today we invite you to escape reality and soak up the serenity of our white-hued landscapes instead. Whether it’s a wombat wandering through #MtKosciuszko’s powdery alpine peaks or stunning @sydney harbour views, we’re certain you’ll find peace of mind whilst immersing yourself in the sounds and sights of our country via Australia in 8D.🕊️ Start planning your next relaxing getaway via the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.text: There’s no doubt about it, pink certainly suits Australia 💕 We couldn’t help but spread the love, or should we say, the lovely feeling, that these magical #magenta scenes from across our country invoke. Allow yourself a little time to marvel at the striking hues of @westernaustralia’s pink lake, take in the @visitgreatoceanroad and @australiasnorthwest's candy-coloured #sunset skies and savour the serenity of @tropicalnorthqueensland, as you fall head over heels with Australia in 8D 😍 To experience dreamy pastel-hued moments like this for yourself, head to the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.text: Breathe in, breathe out … your tranquil adventure through our lush landscapes starts here 😌 Inspired by shades of green, today we’re transporting you to some of the most calming and captivating destinations across Australia, from @tropicalnorthqueensland's ancient rainforest and @rottnestislandwa’s quokka-filled shores, to the magnificent @visitbluemountains and ruggedly beautiful @ntaustralia. Sit back and immerse yourself in the raw and rejuvenating sights and sounds of Australia in 8D; we like to think of it as natural therapy, and relaxation is guaranteed 💚. For more inspiration on how to plan your next nature-based getaway, head to the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.text: Today we’re rolling out Australia’s red carpet, just for you ❤️ Scarlet, cerise, ruby… call it what you like, it’s an unforgettable hue that can be found in abundance along the road less travelled in our big, bold and beautiful backyard. Take in the sights and sounds of the @ntaustralia’s aptly named #RedCentre and be amazed by the @australiasnorthwest #HorizontalFalls, via Australia in 8D. Feeling inspired to plan your own colourful adventure? Head to the link in our bio to discover more of Australia’s striking scenery. #seeaustralia

node.text: If you’re into mystery and thrills, step right this way... 🖤 There’s just something about @visitmelbourne’s sparkling city skyline and the pitter-patter of penguins exploring #PhillipIsland at dusk that leaves you wanting more. Feel the suspense that the patterns, textures and sounds of the @ngvmelbourne invoke, and allow your breath to be taken away by the sheer power of #KakaduNationalPark’s waterfalls in @ntaustralia. Elegant and bold, Australia’s landscapes with a touch of black demand to be seen and explored via Australia in 8D 😎 To create your own adventure inspired by this dark and mystical hue, click the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.text: From wide-open skies to vast expanses of sea, Australia’s many shades of blue are simply irresistible 💙 Today we’re inviting you to dip your toes into our calming oceans, picturesque pools and idyllic island shores. Play with Australian Sea Lions at #BairdBay in @southaustralia, discover the colourful wonders of the @gbrmarinepark, see dolphins surfing the sparkling waves of @AustraliasGoldenOutback, and listen in awe to whales singing in @visitfrasercoast. Now is the time to escape reality and soak up the blissful-blues of Australia in 8D. To discover more holiday ideas inspired by this refreshing hue, click the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: Blue: A Moment of Joy - 8D Escapes

node.text: Deep breath, and relaaaaaax 🧘 This serene scene comes courtesy of #EmmaGorge in @australiasnorthwest, snapped by @overlandxexplorers at the start of their Gibb River Road adventure. A true outback odyssey, the #GibbRiverRoad runs from Derby to Kununurra (or Wyndham) in @westernaustralia, and is one of Australia’s most unique 4WD tracks. Originally constructed in the 1960s to transport cattle, the 660km trail is one of the best ways to discover the natural treasures of the Kimberley. #seeaustralia #thisiswa #australiasnorthwest #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Another day, another epic @officialfleurieupeninsula landscape! 🤩 Thanks to @imlukemackenzie for capturing this stunning shot of #SellicksBeach in @southaustralia. Less than an hour from @cityofadelaide and just a stone's throw from the vineyards of #McLarenVale, this coastal playground is a favourite amongst locals and visitors alike. One look at this shot and it's easy to see why it's one of the most photographed stretches of coastline on the #FleurieuPeninsula! 📸 #seeaustralia #seesouthaustralia #FleurieuPeninsula #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Please teleport us to @tarakilodge right now 🙏 Well known for its rugged scenery and seriously scrumptious seafood, spend your days exploring @visitnorthwesttasmania's #KingIsland, before soaking in the epic ocean views and luxury accommodation on offer at Taraki Lodge. Your biggest decision when staying at this incredible spot in @tasmania will be whether to try the hot tub or the sauna first... it's a tough life, but somebody's gotta do it! 😉 #seeaustralia #discovertasmania #northwesttasmania #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Breakfast in bed never looked so cute! 🐨 🌱 Say hello to Pixie the koala joey who is being lovingly hand-raised by @timswildlife from the @australianreptilepark in @lovecentralcoastnsw. Not only does this @visitnsw wildlife park rescue and care for wildlife, but they also run a koala conservation breeding program to ensure this very special animal sticks around for years to come! FACT: An adult koala eats between 200 to 500 grams of leaves each day - talk about getting your greens in! 🥗 #seeaustralia #LoveNSW #LoveCentralCoast #holidayherethisyear

node.text: We know it's rude to stare but with views like this, who can blame us? 😉 The local Butchella people refer to @visitfraserisland as K'Gari, meaning 'paradise', and we'd have to agree! Captured here by @kyle_hunter, this @queensland island is best explored via 4WD. Set off on a self-guided adventure or jump on a 4WD bus with @fraserexplorertours to see the island's most iconic sites, including #LakeMcKenzie and #75milebeach. To view @visitfrasercoast from above, take to the air on a scenic flight with @airfraserisland. #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #frasercoast #visitfraserisland #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Oh, #KingsCanyon, you’re blooming beautiful! 😍 @treasureearthco captured this gorgeous scene on a recent visit to Watarrka National Park in @visitcentralaus. Home to the Luritja and Arrente people, Kings Canyon can be found halfway between #AliceSprings and #Uluru in @ntaustralia. For epic views of the gorge and the surrounding landscape below, the 6km Kings Canyon Rim Walk is a must. Our tip: rise early before the heat to catch the sunrise from the top! #seeaustralia #RedCentreNT #NTaustralia #holidayherethisyear

node.text: "But mum, my legs are tired!" 🐨😂 While leading a tour with @kangarooislandodysseys, @nikkiki73 caught this little #koala joey hitching a ride with mum. This cutie is one of the new joeys to be born on @authentickangarooisland this season, which is a wildlife haven and fabulous place to see an array of Aussie animals in the wild. You'll find plenty of koalas as well as kangaroos, Wedge-tailed Eagles, and echidnas on this @southaustralia island, as well as the famous sea lions at @sealbay. #seeaustralia #seesouthaustralia #KangarooIsland #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Thank you for delivering the serenity we needed today @queensland 🙏 @wilsonarcherfilms captured this stellar shot while visiting @mountmulliganlodge in @tropicalnorthqueensland. Set on a 28,000-hectare cattle station, this @luxurylodgesofaustralia property accommodates just 20 guests at any one time, making for a seriously relaxing and private getaway. Reach this dreamy spot via a 35-minute scenic helicopter flight from #Cairns or by hopping in a 4WD for a 2.5-hour road trip. #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #exploreTNQ #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Well, aren't you looking rather sun-sational @eyrepeninsula! ☀️ Thanks to @elleschembri for capturing this stunning shot of the Yanerbie sand dunes near #StreakyBay in @southaustralia. Home to the Wirungu people, follow the Westall Way Loop scenic drive and watch this spectacular stretch of coastline unfold before you. There are plenty of photogenic natural attractions to be found on this route, so be prepared to get snap happy 📸 #seeaustralia #SeeSouthAustralia #eyrepeninsula #HolidayHereThisYear

node.text: "Follow me! I know all the best swimming spots!" 🐢 While swimming in the clear waters of #HamiltonIsland, @little.gypsies got a special guided tour from this friendly chap. Sea turtles can be found in the @whitsundaysqld all year round and choose to nest and lay eggs on the sands of the various lovely islands in this part of @queensland. Want to see one of these fascinating creatures for yourself? Book in on Turtle Discovery tour with @hamiltonisland and explore the beautiful, fringing reefs while keeping an eye out for a turtle or two 👀#seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #lovewhitsundays #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Why hello spring, we meet again! 🌸 It's the first day of spring here in Australia, which means sunny days, cool nights, colourful flowers and, of course, adorable baby animals 😍 The change of season has definitely arrived on @authentickangarooisland, where @nikkiki73 spotted this furry fellow frolicking amongst the blooms while guiding a @kangarooislandodysseys tour. Located off the coast of @southaustralia, #KangarooIsland is an incredible destination all year round, but is particularly lovely at this time of year. #seeaustralia #SeeSouthAustralia #authenticKI #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Are we biased, or is @seeuluru looking mighty fine this evening? 😍 Thanks to @tessomewhere for delivering this dreamy view of @ntaustralia's iconic #RedCentre, home to the local Anangu people. Taken high above @visitcentralaus' #UluruKataTjutaNationalPark on a scenic flight, you too can witness the ancient wonders of #Uluru and #KataTjuta rise from the earth in all their brightly hued glory! Take your adventure to the next level with @ayersrockscenicflights, @outback_ballooning or @ayersrockhelicopters 🚁 #seeaustralia #NTaustralia #RedCentreNT #SeeUluru #holidayherethisyear
